CopyFunction.document:
This API is used to replicate a function. You can store the replicated function in a specified Region and Namespace.
Note: This API **does not** replicate the following objects or attributes of the function:
1. Function trigger
2. Versions other than $LATEST
3. CLS target of the logs configured in the function

You can manually configure the function after replication as required.
CopyFunction.name: Replicates a function

CreateAlias.document:
This API is used to create an alias for a function version. You can use the alias to mark a specific function version such as DEV/RELEASE. You can also modify the version pointed to by the alias at any time.
An alias must point to a master version and can point to an additional version at the same time. If you specify an alias when invoking a function, the request will be sent to the versions pointed to by the alias. You can configure the ratio between the master version and additional version during request sending.
CreateAlias.name: Creates alias for function version

CreateNamespace.document: This API is used to create a namespace based on the input parameters.
CreateNamespace.name: Creates a namespace

CreateTrigger.document: This API is used to create a trigger based on the input parameters.
CreateTrigger.name: Creates a function trigger

DeleteAlias.document: This API is used to delete an alias of a function version.
DeleteAlias.name: Deletes alias

DeleteFunction.document: This API is used to delete a function based on the input parameters.
DeleteFunction.name: Deletes a function

DeleteLayerVersion.document: This API is used to delete a specified version of a specified layer. The deleted version cannot be associated with a function, but the deletion does not affect functions that are referencing this layer.
DeleteLayerVersion.name: Deletes layer version

DeleteNamespace.document: This API is used to delete the specific namespace according to the parameters passed in.
DeleteNamespace.name: Deletes a namespace

DeleteProvisionedConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to delete the provisioned concurrency configuration of a function version.
DeleteProvisionedConcurrencyConfig.name: Deletes provisioned concurrency

DeleteReservedConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to delete the configuration of reserved quota.
DeleteReservedConcurrencyConfig.name: Removes the reserved quota of a function

DeleteTrigger.document: This API is used to delete an existing trigger based on the input parameters.
DeleteTrigger.name: Deletes a trigger

GetAccount.document: This API is used to get the account information.
GetAccount.name: Gets account information

GetAlias.document: This API is used to get the alias details such as the name, description, version, and routing information.
GetAlias.name: Gets alias details

GetAsyncEventStatus.document: This API is used to get the status of an async function execution event. The event status is retained for 3*24 hours, counting from the completion of the event.
GetAsyncEventStatus.name: Gets the async event status of a function

GetFunctionAddress.document: This API is used to obtain the download address of the function code package.
GetFunctionAddress.name: Obtains download address of the function code

GetFunctionEventInvokeConfig.document: This API is used to get the async retry configuration of a function, including the number of retry attempts and message retention period.
GetFunctionEventInvokeConfig.name: Gets the async retry configuration of function

GetFunctionLogs.document: This API returns function running logs according to the specified conditions. Note that this API has been disused. You can use [GetRequestStatus](https://intl.cloud.tencent.com/document/product/583/65348?from_cn_redirect=1) instead. See also [Retrieving Logs](https://intl.cloud.tencent.com/document/product/583/52637?from_cn_redirect=1).
GetFunctionLogs.name: Obtains a function running log

GetLayerVersion.document: This API is used to get the layer version details, including links used to download files in the layer.
GetLayerVersion.name: Gets layer version details

GetProvisionedConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to get the provisioned concurrency details of a function or its specified version.
GetProvisionedConcurrencyConfig.name: Gets the provisioned concurrency details of function

GetRequestStatus.document: This API is used to query the status of a single function request.
GetRequestStatus.name: Queries the status of a single function request.

GetReservedConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to obtain the reserved quota details of a function.
GetReservedConcurrencyConfig.name: Obtains the reserved quota details of a function

Invoke.document: This API is used to run a function.
Invoke.name: Runs a function

InvokeFunction.document: This API is used to invoke functions synchronously.
InvokeFunction.name: Invokes functions synchronously

ListAliases.document: This API is used to return the list of all aliases under a function. You can filter them by the specific function version.
ListAliases.name: Gets alias list

ListAsyncEvents.document: This API is used to pull the list of async function events.
ListAsyncEvents.name: Pulls async function event list

ListFunctions.document: This API is used to return relevant function information based on the input query parameters.
ListFunctions.name: Obtains a function list

ListLayerVersions.document: This API is used to get the information of all versions of a specified layer.
ListLayerVersions.name: Gets layer version list

ListLayers.document: This API is used to return the list of all layers, including the information of the latest version of each layer. You can filter them by the compatible runtime.
ListLayers.name: Returns layer list

ListNamespaces.document: This API is used to display a namespace list.
ListNamespaces.name: Displays a namespace list

ListTriggers.document: This API is used to get the function trigger list.
ListTriggers.name: Gets function trigger list

ListVersionByFunction.document: This API is used to query the function version based on the input parameters.
ListVersionByFunction.name: Queries a function version

PublishLayerVersion.document: This API is used to create a version for a layer by using the given .zip file or COS object. Each time this API is called with the same layer name, a new version will be generated.
PublishLayerVersion.name: Publishes layer version

PublishVersion.document: This API is used for users to release a new version of the function.
PublishVersion.name: Releases a new version

PutProvisionedConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to set the provisioned concurrency of a non-$LATEST version of a function.
PutProvisionedConcurrencyConfig.name: Sets provisioned concurrency

PutReservedConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to configure the reserved quota of a function.
PutReservedConcurrencyConfig.name: Configures the reserved quota

PutTotalConcurrencyConfig.document: This API is used to modify the account concurrency quota.
PutTotalConcurrencyConfig.name: Modifies account concurrency quota

TerminateAsyncEvent.document: This API is used to terminate a running async function event.
TerminateAsyncEvent.name: Terminates async function event

UpdateAlias.document: This API is used to update the configuration of an alias.
UpdateAlias.name: Updates alias configuration

UpdateFunctionCode.document: This API is used to update the function code based on the input parameters.
UpdateFunctionCode.name: Updates the function code

UpdateFunctionEventInvokeConfig.document: This API is used to update the async retry configuration of a function, including the number of retry attempts and message retention period.
UpdateFunctionEventInvokeConfig.name: Updates the async retry configuration of function

UpdateNamespace.document: This API is used to update a namespace.
UpdateNamespace.name: Updates a namespace

UpdateTriggerStatus.document: This API is used to update the trigger status.
UpdateTriggerStatus.name: Updates the trigger tatus

Filter.document:
Key-value pair filters for conditional filtering queries, such as filtering ID, name, and status.
If more than one filter exists, the logical relationship between these filters is `AND`.
If multiple values exist in one filter, the logical relationship between these values under the same filter is `OR`.

members.document:
Fields to be filtered. Up to 10 conditions allowed.
Values of `Name`: `VpcId`, `SubnetId`, `ClsTopicId`, `ClsLogsetId`, `Role`, `CfsId`, `CfsMountInsId`, `Eip`. Values limit: 1.
Name options: Status, Runtime, FunctionType, PublicNetStatus, AsyncRunEnable, TraceEnable. Values limit: 20.
When `Name` is `Runtime`, `CustomImage` refers to the image type function

members.document:
Values of `filter.RetCode` include:
not0, indicating that only logs of failed execution will be returned.
is0, indicating that only logs of successful execution will be returned.
TimeLimitExceeded, indicating that logs of function invocations which timed out will be returned.
ResourceLimitExceeded, indicating that logs of function invocations during which resources exceeded the upper limit will be returned.
UserCodeException, indicating that logs of function invocations during which a user code error occurred will be returned.
Blank, indicating that all logs will be returned.

Matching rule key. When the API is called, pass in the `key` to route the request to the specified version based on the matching rule
Header method:
Enter "invoke.headers.User" for `key` and pass in `RoutingKey:{"User":"value"}` when invoking a function through `invoke` for invocation based on rule matching
members.name: Key

members.document:
Match method. Valid values:
range: range match
exact: exact string match
members.name: Method

members.document:
Rule requirements for range match:
It should be described in an open or closed range, i.e., `(a,b)` or `[a,b]`, where both a and b are integers
Rule requirements for exact match:
Exact string match
